headline: RH Q3 Earnings Miss Estimates, Revenues Beat, FY25 Guidance Lowered
summary: RH posts mixed Q3 results as earnings slip but revenues rise YoY, with lowered FY25 guidance highlighting tariff and housing pressures.

headline: Assessing Williams-Sonoma (WSM) Valuation After a Recent Share Price Rebound
summary: Williams-Sonoma (WSM) has been quietly treading water this month, but its longer history tells a different story, with the stock roughly tripling over the past 3 years despite recent softness. headline: 3 Consumer Stocks with Open Questions
summary: Retailers are evolving to meet the expectations of modern, tech-savvy shoppers. This includes developing an online presence to fend off e-commerce competitors, a strategy that has helped the industry maintain steady demand by giving it more sales channels. In turn, retail stocks were up 20.8% over the past six months compared to 13.9% for the S&P 500.
